ce:section.ce:para:
This dual-mode sensing platform was used to determine the presence of glyphosate and profenofos in two Chinese traditional medicinal herbs (Angelica sinensis, Codonopsis). There was no detected of two OPPs, which was also consistent with the validated results using HPLC-MS. It illustrated that theses samples were not contaminated with glyphosate and profenofos. To investigate the practical application potential of the proposed method, spiked recoveries were investigated by spiking different concentrations of glyphosate and profenofos standard solutions. The favorable recoveries were 100.58 % (RSD＜1.54) in smartphone-based colorimetric sensing mode for the detection of glyphosate (Table 1
                        ), and 99.00 % (RSD＜5.23) in fluorescence sensing mode for the detection of profenofos (Table 2
                        ). The matrix effect (ME) was the ratio of linear slopes in the real sample and in the standard solution. The calculated ME values were ranging from 95.46 % to 100.58 % and 90.05 % to 99.00 %. The desirable result demonstrated the potential application of this colorimetric/fluorescent dual-mode sensing platform in real samples.
